  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. Substituting <math><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn></math> for <em>y</em> in the first equation yields <math><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn></math>. Subtracting <math><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn></math> from both sides gives <math><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, or <math><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Thus <em>x</em> = 0 or <em>x</em> = 1. When <em>x</em> = 0, <em>y</em> = 3(0)+7 = 7, giving the ordered pair (0, 7).</p><p>Choices A, B, and D are incorrect.</p>",
